[This course](https://engineering.purdue.edu/ECE/Academics/Undergraduates/UGO/CourseInfo/courseInfo?courseid=150&show=true&type=grad) introduces the fundamentals of rotating electric machinery and power electronic drives. It covers the theoretical principles of electromechanical energy conversion and offers a rigorous study of major classes of electric machines. Additionally, the course presents the basics of three-phase dc-ac power electronic converters, emphasizing their role in applications ranging from industrial systems to renewable energy and electric vehicles.

